g test plans**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how to handle classpath failures during tests — if one branch fails, values might not be recorded. I need a separate test for the classpathFile specifically. Also, another test should cover all other properties. I'll include handling for potential RuntimeExceptions, especially if the issue is an IllegalArgumentException. My plan should also ensure tests lead to uncovered call sites. I should create separate tests for conversion, plain files, streams, and classpath resources to ensure everything is covered efficiently.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying test expectations**\\\\n\\\\nI'm focusing on ensuring that if success is asserted for the classpathFile to be a file URL, it should trigger an IllegalArgumentException if it fails. However, if the native Class.getResource method returns null, that leads to a RuntimeException indicating the file doesn't exist. It's essential to check for resource metadata as well. I must create a second test for the JVM and verify success at line 190, while considering how the native test handles resource URLs. I need to be cautious about potential failures before reaching that point.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering adjustments to helper functions**\\\\n\\\\nI think I might need to allow for an IllegalArgumentException only. I should write a helper function to get the root cause. Also, the PropertyCapturingWadlGenerator needs to handle reading from the resource stream—it can hit a null pointer exception in classpath-only tests after setting a property, which isn’t ideal. Making the readResourceStream return null when given null could help. After that, I might need to adjust assertions for the resource text.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_djb03Eo1vjtOAuH7YTd3jgoy|fc_0a37af11de3481750169fed982d9e481a39c0ccfabe2fb2e3d\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.sun.jersey/jersey-server/1.9/src/test/java/com_sun_jersey/jersey_server/WadlGeneratorLoaderTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    @Test\\n    void createsConfiguredGeneratorUsingAllSupportedPropertyConversions() {\\n        WadlGeneratorConfig wadlGeneratorConfig = WadlGeneratorConfig\\n                .generator(PropertyCapturingWadlGenerator.class)\\n                .prop(\\\"exactValue\\\", \\\"direct-string\\\")\\n                .prop(\\\"qualifiedName\\\", \\\"converted-name\\\")\\n                .prop(\\\"resourceStream\\\", RESOURCE_NAME)\\n                .prop(\\\"classpathFile\\\", \\\"classpath:/\\\" + RESOURCE_NAME)\\n                .prop(\\\"plainFile\\\", \\\"target/generated-wadl.xml\\\")\\n                .build();\\n\\n        WadlGenerator wadlGenerator = wadlGeneratorConfig.createWadlGenerator();\\n\\n        assertThat(wadlGenerator).isInstanceOf(PropertyCapturingWadlGenerator.class);\\n        assertThat(PropertyCapturingWadlGenerator.configuredValues).hasSize(1);\\n        PropertyValues values = PropertyCapturingWadlGenerator.configuredValues.get(0);\\n        assertThat(values.exactValue).isEqualTo(\\\"direct-string\\\");\\n        assertThat(values.qualifiedName).isEqualTo(new QName(\\\"converted-name\\\"));\\n        assertThat(values.resourceText).contains(\\\"loaded from the test classpath\\\");\\n        assertThat(values.classpathFile).isFile().hasName(RESOURCE_NAME);\\n        assertThat(values.plainFile).isEqualTo(new File(\\\"target/generated-wadl.xml\\\"));\\n        assertThat(values.delegate).isNotNull();\\n    }\\n\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    void createsConfiguredGeneratorUsingSupportedPropertyConversions() {\\n        WadlGeneratorConfig wadlGeneratorConfig = WadlGeneratorConfig\\n                .generator(PropertyCapturingWadlGenerator.class)\\n                .prop(\\\"exactValue\\\", \\\"direct-string\\\")\\n                .prop(\\\"qualifiedName\\\", \\\"converted-name\\\")\\n                .prop(\\\"resourceStream\\\", RESOURC