{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2927-library-new-request-com.sun.jersey-jersey-server-1.9-5dc6d69e\n\nThe main blocker appears to be the test-generation / metadata-generation stage, not the coverage gate. Dynamic-access coverage reached `27/53` (`50.94%`), but the run metrics still show `6` iterations, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, no emitted test/metadata artifacts, and no commit movement. The preserved logs show the generated tests never stabilized: JVM/native test runs failed first in `WadlGeneratorLoaderTest` (`javax/xml/bind/JAXBException`, then missing `wadl-generator-loader-resource.txt`) and later `ContainerFactoryTest` (`ClassNotFoundException: com_sun_jersey.jersey_server.container_factory_support.WebResources`) in `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-09T06-52-48-562050Z.log`, `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-09T07-03-51-267968Z.log`, and `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-09T07-07-57-612300Z.log`.\n\nMetadata collection also failed during follow-up verification: `generateMetadata` could not load `native-image-agent` (`Could not find agent library native-image-agent on the library path`) in `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-09T07-09-43-178878Z.log`. After that, native trace retries still exposed missing registrations for `com_sun_jersey.jersey_server.container_factory_support.WebResources` and its constructor in `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-09T07-09-46-988126Z.log` and `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/native-test-verify/cycle-1-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-09T07-10-15-181869Z.log`. A later retry then failed during native-image compilation with an unexpected `MimeMultipartProvider.<init>` hosted error in `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/native-test-verify/cycle-2-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-09T07-10-50-993379Z.log`. Additional context is in `logs/com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9/metadata-fix/codex.log`.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Fix the generated Jersey 1.9 tests so the required JAXB/runtime deps, `wadl-generator-loader-resource.txt`, and `container_factory_support.WebResources` are present on the actual JVM/native test classpath.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9` and `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=com.sun.jersey:jersey-server:1.9` with a GraalVM setup that has a working `native-image-agent`, then add the missing reflection/resource metadata surfaced by `runNativeTraceImage`.\n3. If the `MimeMultipartProvider.<init>` native-image compile failure still reproduces after the metadata fixes, isolate that separately as a GraalVM/Jersey compatibility problem before finalizing the new-library submission."}}
